  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Integrated mobile outreach response to Cyclone Sagar in Zeylac District, Awdal Region, Somaliland</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">SRCS has long experience in primary health care and nutrition programmes. SRCS health and nutrition programme provides preventative and curative responses to the most vulnerable communities. This project will respond to the needs of cyclone affected communities in Zeila district to provide an integrated health and nutrition services through mobile outreach teams and WASH interventions. lawyacado MCH was badly affected and damaged by the recent Sagar Cyclone and destroyed all its main facilities around the MCH. SRCS with the support of IFRC (International federation of Red cross and Red crescent) will rehabilitate lawyacado MCH building. In addition SRCS will also carry out hygiene and sanitation awareness raising campaigns focusing on household water treatment/behavior change, capacity building of community water management committees, distribution of water filters (clay filter) and aqua tabs for drinking safe water access, training on PHAST for the target communities on good hygiene practices.
The health and nutrition activities will include deployment of three mobile clinics which will provide to cyclone affected people integrated health and nutrition services. The clinics will treat the common health conditions including acute respiratory infections, diarrhoea, skin and eye infections, etc. while severe and moderately malnourished will be also treated accordingly with nutrition supplements. it will target 40050 direct beneficiaries and 32196 indirect beneficiaries living in Zeila district. this will also include women, 16821, men 9211, boys, 6869 and girls 7149 for direct beneficiaries of the project.</narrative>
  </description>
